name: 20 de Noviembre 03
description:
Avenida 20 de Noviembre is a road of the majestic historic center of CDMX drawn up in the first half of the 20th century.

But the idea of creating this avenue was carried out around the year 1936, to commemorate the twenty-sixth anniversary of the Mexican Revolution of 1910.? In order to carry out this avenue, some buildings of historical value dating from the colonial period were demolished, while others were reduced in size, such as the Palace of the Condes de la Cortina or the Temple of San Bernardo, and others of recent bill were raised in the so-called "neocolonial" style.

The woman in the photograph works outside the church of San Bernanrdo selling religious articles
